{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks/task-39","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks","challengeType":19,"description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Before</span> koristi se za razgovor o vremenu ranije od događaja ili ponekad. Pokazuje da nešto dešava se prvo. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">I eat breakfast before I go to work</span> znači da je doručkovanje ranije nego odlazak na posao.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">After</span> se koristi za opisivanje stvari koje se dešavaju nakon događaja ili u nekom drugom trenutku. Pokazuje niz događaja gde nešto sledi nešto drugo. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">I go home after work</span> znači da se dolazak kući dešava nakon završetka posla.</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Around</span> Koristi se sa vremenskim frazama da bi pokazao vreme blizu, ali ne nužno tačno u tom trenutku. Pokazuje fleksibilnost tokom kratkog vremenskog perioda. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">We'll meet around noon</span> može značiti bilo koje vreme blizu 12:00 PM, kao što su 11:45 AM ili 12:15 PM. Često se koristi da bi se dao opšti predaj o vremenu, bez previše specifičnosti.</p>\n</section>","nodules":null,"explanation":null,"helpCategory":"English","instructions":"","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks/task-39"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Anna, kada je pauza za ručak?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Before noon.</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Anna nije rekla da se pauza za ručak dešava rano, pre šest sati popodne.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">After noon.</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Podne je 12:00 PM, a Anna nije rekla da pauza počinje posle tog vremena.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Just before work ends.</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Pauza za ručak su usred dana, a ne kraj radnog dana.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Around noon.</span></p>","feedback":null,"audioId":null}],"solution":4}],"scene":{"setup":{"background":"interview-room3.png","characters":[{"character":"Anna","position":{"x":50,"y":15,"z":1.2},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"2.1-2.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":32.36,"finishTimestamp":35.02},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"Anna","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Anna","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":3.66,"dialogue":{"text":"You have a one-hour lunch break around noon every day.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Anna","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":4.16,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","tests":[],"title":"Vežba 39","transcript":null,"translationPending":false,"videoId":null,"videoLocaleIds":null}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/#learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks","dashedName":"task-39","certification":"a2-english-for-developers","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks/task-40","prevChallengePath":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-talk-about-a-typical-workday-and-tasks/task-38","id":"657e2c85b80142efb0dcb6fa","saveSubmissionToDB":nu